Load Dataset and Packages

Code 
# load package(s)
library(tidyverse)

# load data
data <- read.csv("data/data.csv")

Building the plot

Code 
new_data <- data %>% 
  pivot_longer(!Year)

ggplot(data = new_data, aes(x = Year, y = value)) + 
  geom_line(aes(group = name, linetype = name)) +
  scale_y_reverse(
    expand = c(0, 0),
    limits = c(100, 0),
    breaks = seq(0, 100, 5)
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    expand = c(0, 0),
    limits = c(1790, 1890),
    breaks = seq(1790, 1890, 10)
  ) +
  coord_flip() +
  theme_light() +
  # theme adjustments come from https://rpubs.com/leeolney/duboischallenge
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom", 
    # remove ticks on x and y axis
    axis.ticks = element_blank(),
    # remove minor grid lines
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    # make major grid lines red with thickness of 0.2
    panel.grid = element_line(size = 0.2, color = "red"),
    # center the plot title with 13.5 size font and bolded
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 13.5, face = "bold"),
    # set width of legend keys to 2.2 cm
    legend.key.width = unit(2.2, "cm"),
    # set spacing between legend keys to 1.5 cm
    legend.spacing = unit(1.5, "cm"),
    # background color of plot = light brown
    plot.background=element_rect(fill="#ead4bc"),
    # background color of plot panel = light brown
    panel.background = element_rect(fill="#ead4bc"),
    # background color of legend = light brown
    legend.background = element_rect(fill="#ead4bc"),
    # background color of legend keys = light brown
    legend.key =element_rect(fill="#ead4bc"),
    # font size of x axis title = 8 with grey color
    axis.title.x = element_text(size  = 8, color = "grey50"),
    # set margin of 2 cm on right side of legend text
    legend.text = element_text(margin = margin(r = 2, unit = "cm")),
    # sets margins of plot to 20 pixels on top and bottom, 80 on the right, 50 on the left
    plot.margin = margin(20, 80, 20, 70),
    # remove legend title
    legend.title = element_blank()
  ) +
  labs(x = NULL, y = "PERCENTS",
       title = "COMPARATIVE INCREASE OF WHITE AND COLORED\nPOPULATION OF GEORGIA")
